      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Read all safety warnings and instructions before use.</strong> Failure to follow warnings and instructions may result in electric shock, fire, and/or serious injury.
      </div>

      <h3>Required Personal Safety Equipment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Face mask</li>
        <li>Safety gloves</li>
        <li>Ear protection</li>
        <li>Safety glasses</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Work Area Safety</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep work area clean and well lit.</li>
        <li>Do not operate in explosive atmospheres or in the presence of flammable liquids, gases, or dust.</li>
        <li>Keep children and bystanders away while operating.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Electrical Safety</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Power tool plugs must match the outlet. Never modify the plug.</li>
        <li>Avoid body contact with grounded surfaces such as pipes, radiators, and refrigerators.</li>
        <li>Do not expose to rain or wet conditions.</li>
        <li>Do not abuse the cord. Never use it for carrying, pulling, or unplugging the tool.</li>
        <li>When operating outdoors, use an extension cord suitable for outdoor use.</li>
        <li>If operating in a damp location is unavoidable, use a residual current device (RCD) protected supply.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Personal Safety</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Stay alert; do not use while tired or under the influence of drugs, alcohol, or medication.</li>
        <li>Always wear eye protection and appropriate protective equipment.</li>
        <li>Prevent unintentional starting &mdash; ensure the switch is off before connecting to power.</li>
        <li>Do not overreach; keep proper footing and balance at all times.</li>
        <li>Do not wear loose clothing or jewelry. Keep hair, clothing, and gloves away from moving parts.</li>
        <li>If devices are provided for dust extraction, ensure they are connected and properly used.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Tool Use and Care</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not overload the tool. Use the correct tool for your application.</li>
        <li>Do not use if the switch does not turn it on and off &mdash; the tool is dangerous and must be repaired.</li>
        <li>Disconnect from power before making adjustments, changing accessories, or storing.</li>
        <li>Store idle tools out of the reach of children.</li>
        <li>Maintain the tool: check for misalignment, binding, breakage, or any condition affecting operation.</li>
        <li>Keep handles and grasping surfaces dry, clean, and free from oil and grease.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Additional Safety Warnings</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Only original Mirka backing pads guarantee tool safety.</li>
        <li>Read the Materials Safety Data Sheet (MSDS) for the work surface.</li>
        <li>If any hand or wrist discomfort is experienced, stop working and seek medical attention.</li>
        <li>Only use an original Mirka power supply cable (non-IEC appliance coupler).</li>
        <li>Check the tool, backing pad, power cord, and fittings regularly for wear.</li>
        <li>Clean or replace the dust extractor collection bag daily &mdash; dust can be highly combustible.</li>
        <li>Always ensure the workpiece is firmly fixed in place.</li>
        <li>Keep hands clear of the spinning accessory during use.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Dust hazard:</strong> Some dust created by power sanding contains chemicals known to cause cancer, birth defects, or other reproductive harm (e.g., lead from lead-based paints, crystalline silica from masonry, arsenic and chromium from treated lumber). Work in a well-ventilated area with approved safety equipment such as dust masks designed to filter microscopic particles.
      </div>

      <h2>Components</h2>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/mirka-deros-650x/p03_00.jpg" alt="Mirka DEROS 650X CV labeled diagram showing all components" />
        <figcaption>Figure 1 &mdash; DEROS 650X CV component layout</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lever</strong> &mdash; Variable speed trigger; press to start, adjust position to control speed</li>
        <li><strong>LED (right)</strong> &mdash; Status indicator (green = ready, red = overload/overtemp)</li>
        <li><strong>LED (left)</strong> &mdash; Bluetooth active indicator</li>
        <li><strong>Hose connection</strong> &mdash; Swivel exhaust for vacuum dust extraction</li>
        <li><strong>Backing pad</strong> &mdash; 150 mm (6") pad, Medium 130 g (Mirka code 8292605011)</li>
        <li><strong>Power cord</strong> &mdash; Rewireable 4.3 m, 100&ndash;120V US</li>
        <li><strong>On/Off</strong> &mdash; Main power switch</li>
        <li><strong>rpm+ / rpm&ndash;</strong> &mdash; Maximum speed adjustment buttons</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Pad Changes</h2>

      <h3>Replacing the Backing Pad</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Disconnect power.</li>
        <li>Insert the pad wrench between the backing pad and brake seal to hold the spindle nut.</li>
        <li>Turn the backing pad counterclockwise to remove it.</li>
        <li>Fit and tighten the new backing pad with washers.</li>
        <li>Remove the pad wrench.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Pad Savers:</strong> Mirka pad savers are placed between the backing pad and the sanding disc to protect the backing pad from wear and tear during aggressive sanding with net products. Change pad savers regularly to prolong backing pad life.
      </div>

      <h3>Replacing the Brake Seal</h3>

      <div class="warning">
        Too much vacuum in your dust extraction system may cause the brake seal to malfunction.
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Remove the backing pad as described above.</li>
        <li>Pull the old brake seal out of its groove.</li>
        <li>Fit the new brake seal in the groove.</li>
        <li>Fit the backing pad as described above.</li>
        <li>Check the brake seal function. The number of washers between the spindle and backing pad can be adjusted to tune brake seal effect.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Speed Settings</h2>
      <p>The DEROS 650X CV operates between 4,000 and 10,000 RPM.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Starting:</strong> Press the On/Off key. The sander LED (right) turns green. Press the lever to start sanding.</li>
        <li><strong>Variable speed:</strong> Adjust the lever position to control speed between 4,000 RPM and the set maximum.</li>
        <li><strong>Adjusting max RPM:</strong> Press <strong>rpm+</strong> or <strong>rpm&ndash;</strong> to increase or decrease the maximum speed by 1,000 RPM per press (range: 4,000&ndash;10,000 RPM).</li>
        <li><strong>Fixed speed mode:</strong> Press <strong>rpm+</strong> and <strong>rpm&ndash;</strong> simultaneously to toggle between variable speed mode (default) and fixed speed mode, where the tool runs at the set max RPM whenever the lever is pressed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Dust Extraction</h2>
      <p>For maximum performance, use the DEROS 650X CV with a Mirka dust extractor (or other suitable extraction unit) and Mirka net sanding products. The combination of Mirka sanders, net sanding products, and dust extractors forms the basis of Mirka dust-free sanding solutions.</p>
      <p>Connect the tool's power cord to the mains supply outlet on the dust extractor to use the extractor's autostart function. The hose connects to the swivel exhaust fitting on the sander.</p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/mirka-deros-650x/p10_03.png" alt="Diagram showing hose connection and pad attachment for the DEROS 650X CV" />
        <figcaption>Figure 2 &mdash; Hose connection and pad fitting detail</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h2>Operation</h2>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/mirka-deros-650x/p10_04.png" alt="DEROS 650X CV operation diagram showing sander usage and component overview" />
        <figcaption>Figure 3 &mdash; Operation overview and component reference</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Ensure the sander is switched off.</li>
        <li>Select a suitable abrasive and secure it to the backing pad, centered. For optimal performance, use a Mirka backing pad with a Mirka net sanding product.</li>
        <li>Switch on the sander by pressing the On/Off key. The sander LED (right) turns green.</li>
        <li>Press the lever to start sanding. Adjust speed with lever position.</li>
        <li>Always place the tool on the work surface <strong>before</strong> starting it, and remove it from the surface <strong>before</strong> stopping it. This prevents gouging due to excess abrasive speed.</li>
        <li>When finished, turn off the sander by pressing the On/Off key. The LED turns off.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/workshop/manuals/mirka-deros-650x/p10_05.jpg" alt="Detail photo showing DEROS 650X CV sanding operation" />
        <figcaption>Figure 4 &mdash; Sander in use detail</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h3>Bluetooth</h3>
      <p>The DEROS 650X CV is equipped with Bluetooth Low Energy technology and can be connected to the MyMirka app for additional tool functionality.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Connect the power cord to mains outlet.</li>
        <li>Press and hold the <strong>Speed+</strong> button while switching the tool on with the On/Off button.</li>
        <li>The left LED lights up green to indicate Bluetooth is active.</li>
        <li>Bluetooth is deactivated when the tool is disconnected from the mains outlet.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        If the MyMirka app is not installed or not available in your country, do not activate Bluetooth.
      </div>

      <h3>Reducing Vibration with Pad Saver or Interface</h3>
      <p>When using a pad saver or interface, vibration levels may increase. The DEROS 650X CV has a balancing screw feature to reduce this vibration:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Disconnect the power cable.</li>
        <li>Remove the backing pad.</li>
        <li>Add hex nuts and screws per the balancing table in the manual (for the DEROS 650, add screws/nuts to positions A, B, C on the spindle).</li>
        <li>Tighten to 2 Nm.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        When the sander is used with an interface, it is recommended to set speed to a maximum of 7,000 RPM.
      </div>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Always disconnect power before maintenance.</strong> Only use original Mirka spare parts.
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backing pad:</strong> Replace when worn. Use pad wrench to remove (counterclockwise) and install new pad with washers.</li>
        <li><strong>Brake seal:</strong> Replace if braking function is lost. Pull old seal from groove, fit new seal, check function.</li>
        <li><strong>Power cord:</strong> Inspect regularly for damage. Only use original Mirka rewireable mains cable (MIE9017211 for US 100&ndash;120V).</li>
        <li><strong>Housing and vents:</strong> Keep cooling air vents clean and free of blockages to ensure air circulation.</li>
        <li><strong>Motor housing:</strong> Any maintenance or repair requiring the motor housing to be opened must be carried out by an authorized Mirka service centre.</li>
      </ul>

