      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Sander LED (right) flashes between red and green</td>
            <td>Connected to a mains outlet with wrong voltage</td>
            <td>Connect to a mains outlet that corresponds with the nominal voltage of the tool (100&ndash;120 VAC)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>No light from sander LED (right) when switched on</td>
            <td>Power cord not properly attached to the sander or mains socket</td>
            <td>Connect it properly</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sander LED (right) is red and sander slows down to 4,000 RPM</td>
            <td>Temperature too high; too heavy long-term load</td>
            <td>Reduce the load for some time and the sander will speed up again</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sander LED (right) is red and RPM is slightly reduced</td>
            <td>Too heavy short-term load</td>
            <td>Use lighter load and the LED will automatically change to green</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Brake seal does not work</td>
            <td>Worn out brake seal or damaged spindle bearing</td>
            <td>Check and replace brake seal or spindle bearing if necessary</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sander has stopped and LED (right) is red</td>
            <td>Tool is in safety mode due to high temperature</td>
            <td>Wait until the tool has cooled down</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

